IT Budget




AutoNation, Inc. (AutoNation), operates as an automotive retailer in the US. The company offers a range of automotive products and services through affiliated dealerships throughout the US.  AutoNation's holdings include 265 stores and 372 franchises.

AutoNation is focused on acquiring regional… MoreAutoNation, Inc. (AutoNation), operates as an automotive retailer in the US. The company offers a range of automotive products and services through affiliated dealerships throughout the US.  AutoNation's holdings include 265 stores and 372 franchises.

AutoNation is focused on acquiring regional franchises and dealerships.  Acquisitions include 16 stores in 2015 and 12 in 2016.
AutoNation's IT department supports a variety of dealerships owned by the company, though the staff is centralized in the corporate headquarters. Several major groups within the department are responsible for broad IT functions, including IT Business Process Change, Business Analytics,… MoreAutoNation's IT department supports a variety of dealerships owned by the company, though the staff is centralized in the corporate headquarters. Several major groups within the department are responsible for broad IT functions, including IT Business Process Change, Business Analytics, Architecture, and Voice and Data Communications, which includes the company's help desk.

In addition, several teams focus on Financial Applications, Customized Application Development, and Sourced Solutions.

An IT Procurement team focuses on selecting and evaluating hardware for use at headquarters and at all dealerships in the US.

The IT Audit team is responsible for audits, consulting reviews, and special projects of technology activities, as well as financial, compliance and operational processes.

Each dealership owned by AutoNation connects to the central server located at headquarters through remote access software.

For 2013, the company is investing in database architecture as well as agile-based SharePoint development. The company is enhancing web and mobile sites.





