From its founding by entrepreneur H. Wayne Huizenga[3] in 1996, AutoNation has become the largest automotive retailer in the United States and is the leading provider of new and pre-owned vehicles and associated services in the United States.[4] The company currently owns and operates over 360 centers of retail operations throughout the continental U.S. and is currently led from its Ft Lauderdale, Florida headquarters by the Chairman, Chief Executive Officer Mike Jackson, former President of Mercedes-Benz North America.
The Executive Vice President of Sales and Chief Operations Officer is Mr. Lance Iserman.



Contents


1 Company operations

1.1 Revenue by Product Category [8]


2 History
3 Notes
4 Further reading
5 External links



Company operations[edit]
AutoNation has over 26,000 employees.[citation needed] who sell and repair 35 different manufacturer brands in 15 states.[5] It is ranked #136 in the 2016 Fortune 500.[6] The company has a large internet presence, offering its entire inventory for online searching.[7]
Revenue by Product Category [8][edit]


